The paper presents a novel CNN-based image editing strategy that allows the user to change the semantic information of an image over an arbitrary region by manipulating the feature-space representation of the image in a trained GAN model. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and generative adversarial networks (GANs). The paper also mentions experiments on various types of GANs trained on different datasets, which suggests machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves image manipulation and editing, which could fall under graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM) sub-categories.
